---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Jesús Quevedo — DevOps Engineer & AI Engineer at Oracle">
  <section class="article" style="padding-bottom:4rem;">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">$ cat about.txt</p>
      <h1 class="section-title">About</h1>
      <div class="section-line"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="article-content" style="margin-top:2rem;">
      <p>
        I build platforms that engineering teams can actually trust —
        and the AI systems that make them smarter.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over 9+ years, I've gone from containerizing legacy Java apps to founding
        DevOps practices from zero, leading full on-prem to AWS migrations, and
        training engineers into DevOps roles. Today at
        <strong style="color:var(--accent)">Oracle</strong>, I'm modernizing legacy
        systems (ClearCase → Git) and driving AI integration into DevOps workflows
        — building a multi-agent RCA system with an Orchestrator-Workers-Auditor
        architecture, aligned with Oracle's company-wide AI adoption initiative.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm pursuing a <strong style="color:var(--accent)">Master's in Artificial Intelligence</strong>
        at UNIR, and I'm already applying what I learn: building predictive models for
        log analysis, designing NLP pipelines for error classification, and integrating
        ML into enterprise CI/CD workflows. My goal is to bridge the gap between
        DevOps and AI — making infrastructure not just automated, but intelligent.
      </p>

      <h2><span class="terminal-prompt">$</span> skills --list</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cloud & Infrastructure:</strong> AWS (EKS, ECS, Lambda, S3, RDS), OCI, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Helm</li>
        <li><strong>CI/CD & Automation:</strong> Jenkins, GitHub Actions, Ansible, Fastlane — reduced pipeline execution times by 35% and taken mobile releases from weekly to daily</li>
        <li><strong>Observability & SRE:</strong> Prometheus, OpenTelemetry, Dynatrace, Grafana, CloudWatch, Kibana — monitoring 20+ production services</li>
        <li><strong>Languages:</strong> Python, Go, Java, Shell, PL/SQL, NodeJS</li>
        <li><strong>AI / ML Engineering:</strong> Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, MLflow, FastAPI, Pandas, NLP, LLMs — building anomaly detection and predictive models. Developing MCP servers with FastMCP</li>
        <li><strong>Leadership:</strong> Built DevOps from zero at Macropay — led on-prem → AWS migration, trained devs into DevOps roles, managed 15 engineers across 30+ microservices</li>
      </ul>

      <h2><span class="terminal-prompt">$</span> grep -r "industry" ./career</h2>
      <p>
        Banking (Santander, HSBC), Fintech (Macropay), Media (TV Azteca),
        Enterprise (Oracle, Macropay), Government.
      </p>

      <h2><span class="terminal-prompt">$</span> cat ai_engineering.md</h2>
      <p>
        AI isn't a side quest for me — it's the other half of what I do.
        At Oracle, I'm building a multi-agent RCA system for CI/CD pipelines —
        three agent roles (Orchestrator, Workers, Auditor) collaborate through
        Agent Gateway and MCP Gateway to analyze logs, generate root cause
        analysis, and validate results against hallucination.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm also pursuing a <strong style="color:var(--accent)">Master's in Artificial Intelligence</strong>
        at UNIR, which gives me the theoretical foundation to go deeper:
        NLP for error classification, time-series analysis for infrastructure
        metrics, and the path toward self-healing systems.
      </p>

      <h2><span class="terminal-prompt">$</span> cat education.log</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Master's in Artificial Intelligence</strong> — UNIR (In Progress)</li>
        <li><strong>B.S. Computer Engineering</strong> — IPN ESIME Culhuacan (2020)</li>
        <li><strong>Digital Systems Technician</strong> — IPN CECyT 9 (2015)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2><span class="terminal-prompt">$</span> cat certs.yaml</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Python Essentials for MLOps — Duke University (2025)</li>
        <li>OCI 2025 Certified AI Foundations Associate — Oracle (2025)</li>
        <li>OCI 2025 Certified Foundations Associate — Oracle (2025)</li>
        <li>OCI DevOps <span style="color:var(--accent); font-size:0.8rem;">(In Progress)</span></li>
      </ul>

      <div style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <a href={`${base}resume/`} class="btn btn-primary">cat resume.pdf &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
